Brief Hospital Course:
Ms ___ was admitted to the colorectal surgery service on 
___ after undergoing a planned laparoscopic right 
hemicolectomy. She tolerated the procedure well and was 
extubated in the OR prior to recovering in the PACU. For full 
details of the procedure please see the dictated operative 
report. That evening she was noted to be hypotensive and 
tachycardic unresponsive to a 1L fluid bolus. Her Hct was 25.7 
for which she received 2 U PRBC. She was taken back that evening 
to the OR for an exploratory laparotomy where she was noted to 
have a bleeding mesenteric blood vessel, which was ligated. Her 
post op Hct was 35.9 with improved hemodynamic stability. She 
was extubated in the OR but was taken to the ICU for monitoring 
overnight. Post op she was kept NPO with IVF and a foley. Her 
Hct was checked every 4 hours and slowly trended down over POD 1 
from 35.9 to 33.3 to 29.7. Because she remained hemodynamically 
stable she was transferred to the main surgical floor that 
evening and her diet was advanced to sips. On POD 2 her diet was 
advanced to clears and she was put on maintenance IV fluids. The 
nusring staff continued to attempt to wean her O2 however, she 
was 89% on room air, she denied shortness of breath. THe patient 
had recieved a large amount of volume when taken to the 
operating room for the second time and this was thought to be 
the cause of the oxygen requirment. By the morning of 
post-operative day three, the patient was weaned from O2 and her 
saturation was 96% on room air. Her lungs were clear bilaterally 
to ascultation. The patient reported passing flatus on the 
morning of post-opreative day three. She was given a regular 
diet which she tolerated well. She was ambulating the inpatient 
unit independently. The patient was hemodynamically stable but 
in the afternoon, she reported feeling week. Given her hospital 
course, discharge was postponed, and the patient was monitored 
overnight. On the morning of ___, the patient's hematocrit 
was 28.9 which was stable from 48 hours before which was 28.6. 
She was tolerating a regular diet and discharged home with 
appropriate discharge instructions.  

